/TobyThyerPhotography-33.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214535/TobyThyerPhotography-33-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-33\" data-attachment-id=\"652814\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214535/TobyThyerPhotography-33.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-33-18/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214535/TobyThyerPhotography-33-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eA forklift was used to shift a JDM Mercedes-Benz Unimog 411 out of the way, but I was glad to keep it in my frame. Presumably a parallel import from the late 1950s, the Unimog’s portal axles are perfect for Japan’s mountainous terrain. A favourite of farmers and emergency services, these quirky machines are still used by Shinkansen rail construction crews today.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy now, you might be beginning to understand Keiji-san’s impressive mechanical expertise. And the projects he takes on are as eclectic as they come.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215020/TobyThyerPhotography-90-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-90\" data-attachment-id=\"652871\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215020/TobyThyerPhotography-90.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-90-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215020/TobyThyerPhotography-90.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214959/TobyThyerPhotography-86-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-86\" data-attachment-id=\"652867\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214959/TobyThyerPhotography-86.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-86-7/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214959/TobyThyerPhotography-86.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214932/TobyThyerPhotography-81-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-81\" data-attachment-id=\"652862\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214932/TobyThyerPhotography-81.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-81-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214932/TobyThyerPhotography-81.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215222/TobyThyerPhotography-111-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-111\" data-attachment-id=\"652892\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215222/TobyThyerPhotography-111.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-111-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215222/TobyThyerPhotography-111-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214911/TobyThyerPhotography-77-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-77\" data-attachment-id=\"652858\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214911/TobyThyerPhotography-77.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-77-9/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214911/TobyThyerPhotography-77-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214901/TobyThyerPhotography-75-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-75\" data-attachment-id=\"652856\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214901/TobyThyerPhotography-75.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-75-9/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214901/TobyThyerPhotography-75-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cp\u003eStepping inside the unassuming shed transports you back to the glory days of the WRC. \u003cem\u003e“It looks like the Prodrive workshop from 1999!”\u003c/em\u003e exclaims Maeda-san, owner of \u003ca href=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2022/10/happy-birthday-dear-impreza/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eW24 SRT\u003c/a\u003e, as he admires his \u003ca href=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2023/10/just-another-street-driven-wrc-impreza/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003efully restored Prodrive S5\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215049/TobyThyerPhotography-95.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215049/TobyThyerPhotography-95-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-95\" data-attachment-id=\"652876\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215049/TobyThyerPhotography-95.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-95-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215049/TobyThyerPhotography-95-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215037/TobyThyerPhotography-93.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215037/TobyThyerPhotography-93-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-93\" data-attachment-id=\"652874\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215037/TobyThyerPhotography-93.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-93-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215037/TobyThyerPhotography-93-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe unload a box from the back of the Forester: a set of refurbished WRC dampers. They join a collection of new, old stock and used Subaru WRC parts cluttering the workshop. Think carbon fibre air intakes, hub assemblies, body panels, and subframes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215116/TobyThyerPhotography-100-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-100\" data-attachment-id=\"652881\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215116/TobyThyerPhotography-100.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-100-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215116/TobyThyerPhotography-100.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215129/TobyThyerPhotography-102-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-102\" data-attachment-id=\"652883\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215129/TobyThyerPhotography-102.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-102-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215129/TobyThyerPhotography-102.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/07003229/TobyThyerPhotography-310-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-3\" data-attachment-id=\"652905\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/07003229/TobyThyerPhotography-310.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-3-22/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/07003229/TobyThyerPhotography-310-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn the corner, a familiar sight catches my eye: an Impreza Retna, identical to my two-door project car. This was the other vehicle Maeda-san had squirrelled when I bought mine. It’s been completely stripped and is destined to become a WRC replica, complete with original steel wide-body panels from Prodrive for a touch of authenticity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan id=\"chapter-anything-is-possible-just-do-it\"\u003eAnything Is Possible – Just Do It \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214820/TobyThyerPhotography-67.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214820/TobyThyerPhotography-67-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-67\" data-attachment-id=\"652848\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214820/TobyThyerPhotography-67.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-67-10/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214820/TobyThyerPhotography-67-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eKeiji-san is tasked with the replica’s restoration, but he also maintains these priceless rally legends.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214849/TobyThyerPhotography-73.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214849/TobyThyerPhotography-73-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-73\" data-attachment-id=\"652854\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214849/TobyThyerPhotography-73.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-73-10/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214849/TobyThyerPhotography-73-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eYet Keiji-san isn’t just some ex-Prodrive mechanic living out an idyllic retirement in Japan’s mountains; he’s just a very clever man.  Intrigued by the array of rally cars in various stages of repair, I asked Keiji-san how he learnt to fix WRC cars. \u003cem\u003e“I just learnt by doing,”\u003c/em\u003e he replied with a casual shrug.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214801/TobyThyerPhotography-63.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214801/TobyThyerPhotography-63-680x850.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-63\" data-attachment-id=\"652844\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214801/TobyThyerPhotography-63.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-63-12/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06214801/TobyThyerPhotography-63.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215246/TobyThyerPhotography-115-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-115\" data-attachment-id=\"652896\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215246/TobyThyerPhotography-115.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-115-7/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215246/TobyThyerPhotography-115-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215234/TobyThyerPhotography-113-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-113\" data-attachment-id=\"652894\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215234/TobyThyerPhotography-113.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-113-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215234/TobyThyerPhotography-113-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215210/TobyThyerPhotography-109-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-109\" data-attachment-id=\"652890\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215210/TobyThyerPhotography-109.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-109-8/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215210/TobyThyerPhotography-109-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eFair enough. But, I wonder, when parts break, are they still available? \u003cem\u003e“Many parts are still available, like brakes and suspension. But if something else breaks, I just make a replacement or modify something else to work.”\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn a way, Keiji-san’s ingenuity embodies the rally spirit. Images of Colin McRae bashing a bent control arm back into shape with a boulder on the side of a gravel road come to mind.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215309/TobyThyerPhotography-119.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215309/TobyThyerPhotography-119-680x453.jpg\" alt=\"TobyThyerPhotography-119\" data-attachment-id=\"652900\" data-go-fullscreen=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215309/TobyThyerPhotography-119.jpg\" data-can-print=\"true\" data-attachment-url=\"https://www.speedhunters.com/2024/10/workshop-keeping-subaru-wrc-cars-japanese-public-roads/tobythyerphotography-119-7/\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/speedhunters-wp-production/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/06215309/TobyThyerPhotography-119-1200x800.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn the opposite corner, a Safari Rally-spec shell awaits its buckled body panels to be pulled out, set up on the chassis jig, and restored. There was a time when these ex-works cars could be purchased for the price of a well-kept R32 Nissan Skyline GT-R. Those days are long gone; even cars like this mangled wreck have become highly sought after.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m just grateful that places like AION Racing Service exist, where the broken warriors of WRC are rehabilitated and reborn as road-legal reminders of Subaru’s rally history.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eToby Thyer\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\nInstagram \u003ca href=\"http://www.instagram.com/_tobinsta_\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e_tobinsta_\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\ntobythyer.co.uk\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
